{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43c558dc-d72b-4db3-a2fe-1ddfe1e4ad91","content":"## What Happened\n\n`DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS because:\n\n1. **Apple's native crypto frameworks** (Security.framework / CryptoKit) have **never supported DSA**.\n2. Older .NET versions shipped an **OpenSSL-based fallback** (`DSAOpenSsl`) on macOS to fill the gap.\n3. .NET 11 **removed that OpenSSL shim on macOS**, so there's no backend left to service `DSA.Create()`.\n\nThe `SYSLIB0034` deprecation warning (introduced in .NET 7) signaled this was coming.\n\n## How to Fix It\n\n**Option 1 — Bring your own OpenSSL (short-term)**\nIf you just need to keep verifying legacy signatures, load OpenSSL explicitly:\n\n```csharp\nusing System.Security.Cryptography;\n\n// Install OpenSSL via Homebrew: brew install openssl\n// Then point to the dylib:\nusing var dsa = new DSAOpenSsl(DSA.Create(1024).ExportParameters(true));\n```\n\n> This only works if OpenSSL is installed on the macOS host. You'd need to ship/bundle it or document the dependency.\n\n**Option 2 — Use BouncyCastle (recommended for legacy verification)**\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"BouncyCastle.Cryptography\" Version=\"2.*\" />\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\n// Load the public key and verify\nvar signer = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA256withDSA\");\nsigner.Init(forSigning: false, publicKeyParam);\nsigner.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);\nbool valid = signer.VerifySignature(signature);\n```\n\nThis is **cross-platform** with no native dependencies.\n\n**Option 3 — Migrate to a modern algorithm (long-term)**\n\nRe-sign with **ECDSA** or **Ed25519** and retire DSA entirely. This is the only sustainable path — DSA is considered legacy and no major platform vendor is investing in it.\n\n## Summary\n\n| Approach | Effort | Cross-platform | Long-term viability |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `DSAOpenSsl` + brew OpenSSL | Low | ❌ macOS needs OpenSSL | Poor |\n| BouncyCastle | Medium | ✅ | Good (for verification) |\n| Migrate to ECDSA/Ed25519 | High | ✅ | Best |\n\nIf the goal is purely **verifying existing signatures** during a transition period, BouncyCastle is the pragmatic choice. Plan a migration to ECDSA or Ed25519 to eliminate the legacy dependency entirely.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"16fd0f06-22f6-49df-be2f-e8cad514f2cc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue related to DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) and the transition from .NET 10 to .NET 11, specifically on macOS. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a well-known breaking change in .NET. Let me recall the details:\n\nIn .NET 7+, Microsoft started deprecating older cryptographic algorithms. Specifically, regarding DSA on macOS:\n\nApple's macOS (via Security.framework / CommonCrypto) never provided native support for DSA. In older .NET versions, the DSA implementation on macOS used an OpenSSL-based fallback. \n\n\nStarting with .NET 7, Microsoft deprecated DSA functionality and removed the OpenSSL shim that had been providing DSA support on macOS, since Apple's native crypto libraries never supported it anyway. So the real issue is that .NET no longer has a way to implement DSA on macOS without that fallback layer. So the fix depends on the use case: if you need to verify existing DSA signatures, third-party libraries like BouncyCastle can help, or you might load OpenSSL explicitly if available. The real solution is migrating to modern algorithms like RSA, ECDSA, or Ed25519 since DSA is fundamentally unsupported on macOS now. back. At some point .NET removed that OpenSSL fallback on macOS, which is why code using DSA now throws a `PlatformNotSupportedException`. Since this is a straightforward knowledge question, I can provide a direct answer without needing to dig into the codebase.","outputTokens":1654,"requestId":"4015:30C63A:1649CA4:191B281:69F94ACE"},"id":"f7f2299a-b8b0-451f-9f8a-c56611e41e5e","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:42:10.618Z","parentId":"8a89fe98-0c29-4141-8a74-1933fd974b1f"}
